text: The Netherlands women's national under-18 and under-19 is a national youth basketball team of the Netherlands. http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/FIBA/fibaStru/nfLeag/p/nationalfederationnumber/334/nfProf.html It represents The Netherlands in international under-19 and under-18 (under age 19 and under age 18) women's basketball competitions. ==Championships participation== ===FIBA Under-19 World Championship for Women=== {|class="wikitable" |- |2013 FIBA Under-19 World Championship for Women||10th place |- |2015 FIBA Under-19 World Championship for Women||9th place |} ===FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women=== {|class="wikitable" |- |1969 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||10th place |- |1971 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||10th place |- |1973 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||7th place |- |1979 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||11th place |- |1981 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||12th place |- |1984 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||9th place |- |1986 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||7th place |- |2011 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||5th place |- |2012 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||4th place |- |2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||4th place |- |2014 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||6th place |- |2015 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship for Women||8th place |} ==See also== * Netherlands women's national basketball team ==References== Basketball Category:Basketball in the Netherlands Category:Basketball teams in the Netherlands Category:Women's national under-19 basketball teams
